gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Bulls 119, Jazz 117
gameRecap.excerpt: The Bulls defeated the Jazz, 119-117. DeMar DeRozan recorded a game-high 29 points, along with six rebounds and seven assists for the Bulls, while Coby White (25 points, six rebounds, six assists) and Nikola Vucevic (23 points, 12 rebounds) added a combined 48 points in the victory. John Collins tallied a season-high 25 points, along with 13 rebounds for the Jazz in the losing effort. The Bulls have won back-to-back games as they improve to 30-32 on the season, while the Jazz fall to 28-35.
